      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The issue with your code is that it has a nested loop, which results in a time complexity of O(n^2). This is not efficient for large inputs. \n\nHere's an optimized version of your function with a time complexity of O(n):\n\n```python\ndef solve_problem(n):\n    return n * (n + 1) // 2\n```\n\nThis function works by using the mathematical formula for the sum of divisors of a number. It simply calculates the sum of the first `n` positive integers, which is equivalent to the sum of the divisors of `n`. This approach is much faster than your original code, especially for large inputs.\n\nHowever, if you still want to keep the original logic and optimize it, you can use a single loop and a set to store the divisors:\n\n```python\ndef solve_problem(n):\n    divisors = set()\n    for i in range(1, int(n**0.5) + 1):\n        if n % i == 0:\n            divisors.add(i)\n            divisors.add(n // i)\n    return len(divisors)\n```\n\nThis version of the function has a time complexity of O(sqrt(n)) and should pass the big test cases",
